title: Maybe I’m overreacting?
body:
I can’t be the only one thinking that the alive appearance of Pepper, Happy and Rhodey, the original core Iron Man characters and the characters who started the MCU off, all got posters depicting them as alive and not killed by Thanos’ snap, only for it to be a bad omen for Tony’s eventual fate in Endgame?

Surely this could act as a  sign, that all three survived, that Tony has a high chance of dying? 

I’m scared for Tony more than ever.

body: @ everybody: just so you have no regrets when all is said and done, I’m gonna say go absolutely wild with your passion for the MCU in this last month before Endgame. Cringe culture be darned. Go back and read those old favorite fanfics. Pretend it’s 2012 peak fandom again. Rewatch all the movies and loudly quote your favorite lines. Write sappy and over-analytic meta. Literally just go for it our time’s running out
